# /check-deps — Dependency Audit

Are your dependencies safe and up to date?

/check-deps detects your package manager and runs a security audit. Reports
vulnerabilities by severity with actionable fix recommendations.

---

## Step 1: Detect package manager

```bash
[ -f package-lock.json ] && echo "PM: npm"
[ -f yarn.lock ] && echo "PM: yarn"
[ -f pnpm-lock.yaml ] && echo "PM: pnpm"
[ -f bun.lockb ] && echo "PM: bun"
[ -f Pipfile.lock ] && echo "PM: pipenv"
[ -f poetry.lock ] && echo "PM: poetry"
[ -f requirements.txt ] && echo "PM: pip"
[ -f go.sum ] && echo "PM: go"
[ -f Cargo.lock ] && echo "PM: cargo"
[ -f Gemfile.lock ] && echo "PM: bundler"
```

If no lock file found: "No recognized package manager detected. /check-deps
supports npm, yarn, pnpm, bun, pip, pipenv, poetry, go, cargo, and bundler."

---

## Step 2: Run audit

### Node.js (npm/yarn/pnpm/bun)
```bash
npm audit --json 2>/dev/null || yarn audit --json 2>/dev/null || pnpm audit --json 2>/dev/null || bun pm audit 2>/dev/null
```

### Python (pip/pipenv/poetry)
```bash
pip audit --format json 2>/dev/null || pipenv check --json 2>/dev/null || safety check --json 2>/dev/null
```

### Go
```bash
govulncheck ./... 2>/dev/null || go list -m -json all 2>/dev/null
```

### Rust
```bash
cargo audit --json 2>/dev/null
```

### Ruby
```bash
bundle audit check 2>/dev/null
```

---

## Step 3: Check for outdated packages

```bash
# Node
npm outdated --json 2>/dev/null || yarn outdated --json 2>/dev/null

# Python
pip list --outdated --format json 2>/dev/null

# Go
go list -m -u all 2>/dev/null
```

---

