---

## Step 5: Suggest actions

If critical/high vulnerabilities exist, use AskUserQuestion:

```
[N] vulnerabilities found ([M] critical, [K] high).

A) Auto-fix all with safe upgrades (patch/minor only)
B) Show me each fix individually — I'll decide
C) Just the report — I'll handle it manually
```

If A: run the appropriate fix command (`npm audit fix`, `pip install --upgrade`, etc.)
but only for patch/minor bumps. Major version upgrades always require user approval.

---

## Important Rules

- **One-shot only.** Run once, report, done. No background monitoring.
- **Never auto-upgrade major versions.** Major bumps can break APIs. Always ask.
- **Report even if clean.** "0 vulnerabilities, all packages up to date" is useful info.
